document_data.mainbody:
isikin was a feng huang member of the Celestial Bureaucracy.
Misikin was one of the officers of the Qui sub-committee that governed the affairs of the animal population of the Fochu Peninsula under orders of the Ministry of Animal Affairs of the Celestial Bureaucracy. Misikin oversaw the feathered animals. She commanded 30 giant eagles and 10 human slaves, of which 10 eagles were always on patrol. She interacted directly with intruders and asked for tribute to her.
In 1358 DR, one of her human slaves was the body of Setsu Iki.
